title: Grateful Dead Live at Fillmore East on 1970-09-20
description:
Set 1

Uncle John's Band, Deep Elem Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Big Railroad Blues, Dark Hollow, Ripple, To Lay Me Down, Truckin', Rosalie McFall, Cumberland Blues, New Speedway Boogie, Brokedown Palace

Set 2

Casey Jones, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Candyman, Sitting On Top Of The World, Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin', Big Boy Pete, Me & My Uncle, Easy Wind, Sugar Magnolia, Attics Of My Life, Mama Tried, Not Fade Away-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks)-> We Bid You Good Night

First set acoustic with David Grisman and David Nelson on mandolin Other artist(s) on bill: NRPS

reviews.review_text: - Six stars minimum. One of the greatest shows & greatest treatments of a recording ever. Peerless Dead listening experience.

My Last Fillmore Show I think because it’s my last ticket and program. Cannot believe I saved that stuff. It was a memorable night. I recall being thrilled that Nelson and Grisman and others came onstage with the dead for a few numbers and that Phil added his electric bass to the acoustic set. I just loved the shows where NRPS opened for the dead. Whenever we saw that we tried to go. My ticket says I paid $5.25. I was about 8 rows back from the stage. I recall that coming up with $$ fir tics was an issue for me at the time. No comment on that tidbit. After listening to this fine version (and thank you to everyone who did the heavy lifting), go to the previous night and feast your ears on a the 9/19/70 Dark Star. It is sublime.  This entire Fillmore run was EXCELLENT as was February 70 which I got to see too. And Port Chester in this era was just nuts too. I’m rambling.  One more ramble, I can confirm that it is Jerry playing piano on To Lay Me Down.  Saw it with my own eyes.

Thank you Another incredible clean up job by your team.  This is a beautiful show that sounds amazing.  Really, a treat.  I can't recommend it enough.  Hopefully, this becomes the default version of this show.  Much appreciated!!!!
